{221}{}{你能再告诉我一次这个地方的历史吗？ -- Can you tell me the history of this place again?}
#{230}{}{We lived far to the north-east, in the mountains. Our tribe survived there afer the Last Day.}
{230}{}{我们住在遥远的东北部山区。我们的部落最后一天在那里幸存了下来。 -- We lived far to the north-east, in the mountains. Our tribe survived there afer the Last Day.}
#{231}{}{How did you made such a long journey?}
{231}{}{你怎么走了这么长的路？ -- How did you made such a long journey?}
#{232}{}{We came most of the way on a train, but the rails were not strong enough. It left its tracks on the borders of Nevada, near Salt Lake City.}
{232}{}{我们大部分时间是乘火车来的，但铁轨不够坚固。它在靠近盐湖城的内华达州边界留下了足迹。 -- We came most of the way on a train, but the rails were not strong enough. It left its tracks on the borders of Nevada, near Salt Lake City.}
#{233}{}{Tell me more about those times.}
{233}{}{告诉我更多关于那些时代的事。 -- Tell me more about those times.}
#{234}{}{Why did you leave your lands?}
{234}{}{你为什么离开你的土地？ -- Why did you leave your lands?}
#{235}{}{Salt Lake City? Where is that?}
{235}{}{盐湖城？那是哪里？ -- Salt Lake City? Where is that?}
#{236}{}{That's all, thank you.}
{236}{}{就这些，谢谢。 -- That's all, thank you.}
#{237}{}{I will show you on your map. It was a big city in times that gold ruled these lands. It's lost its glory since then, but people still live there.}
{237}{}{我会在地图上指给你看。在黄金统治这些土地的时代，这是一座大城市。从那以后它失去了它的荣耀，但人们仍然住在那里。 -- I will show you on your map. It was a big city in times that gold ruled these lands. It's lost its glory since then, but people still live there.}
#{238}{}{You got the coordinates of Salt Lake City.}
{238}{}{你有盐湖城的坐标。 -- You got the coordinates of Salt Lake City.}
#{239}{}{That was more than thirty years ago. When the Devourer took his tribute across the world, the old ones hid our people in the mountains. We lived through the Last Day there. Many died afterwards, when huge clouds of burning dust hid us from the Ruler of Life. I don't remember that time very well, as I was very young, but... It was horrible.}
{239}{}{那是三十多年前的事了。当吞食者把他的贡品带到世界各地时，古老的人把我们的人民藏在山里。我们在那里度过了最后一天。许多人死后，当巨大的燃烧的灰尘云掩盖了我们对生命的统治者。我不太记得那个时候，因为我很年轻，但是。。。太可怕了。 -- That was more than thirty years ago. When the Devourer took his tribute across the world, the old ones hid our people in the mountains. We lived through the Last Day there. Many died afterwards, when huge clouds of burning dust hid us from the Ruler of Life. I don't remember that time very well, as I was very young, but... It was horrible.}
#{240}{}{The lands themselves stood against us. The mountains made us think of hope, fire and food, but we feared the vicious mutants the most. They attacked settlements and killed everyone. All the remained of people were smashed bodies and torn clothing.}
{240}{}{土地本身与我们作对。群山使我们想到希望、火和食物，但我们最害怕的是邪恶的变种人。他们袭击了定居点，杀死了所有人。剩下的人都是被砸碎的尸体和破衣服。 -- The lands themselves stood against us. The mountains made us think of hope, fire and food, but we feared the vicious mutants the most. They attacked settlements and killed everyone. All the remained of people were smashed bodies and torn clothing.}
#{1130}{}{Stop, wanderer! I am only an old man, and I have nothing. Do not let evil spirits guide you... }
{1130}{}{站住，流浪汉！我只是一个老人，一无所有。别让恶魔指引你。。。 -- Stop, wanderer! I am only an old man, and I have nothing. Do not let evil spirits guide you... }
#{1143}{}{Hmm... I see a child of the Devourer and at the same time, a person who loves our people. I hope you continue to walk the bright path, wanderer... }
{1143}{}{隐马尔可夫模型。。。我看到一个吞食者的孩子，同时，一个爱我们人民的人。我希望你继续走光明的路，流浪者。。。 -- Hmm... I see a child of the Devourer and at the same time, a person who loves our people. I hope you continue to walk the bright path, wanderer... }
#{1144}{}{Our humble camp is open to you, wanderer, so long as you come in peace.}
{1144}{}{我们简陋的营地对你开放，流浪者，只要你能平安地来。 -- Our humble camp is open to you, wanderer, so long as you come in peace.}
#{1145}{}{It is a happy day when you come to our camp, wanderer. How can an old shaman help you?}
{1145}{}{流浪汉，你来到我们的营地真是快乐的一天。一个老巫师怎么能帮你？ -- It is a happy day when you come to our camp, wanderer. How can an old shaman help you?}
#{1152}{}{I'm just out for a walk. What are you doing among the graves?}
{1152}{}{我只是出去走走。你在坟墓里干什么？ -- I'm just out for a walk. What are you doing among the graves?}
#{1154}{}{I was just going. [exit]}
{1154}{}{我正要去。[退出] -- I was just going. [exit]}
#{1189}{}{Be careful, wanderer.}
{1189}{}{小心点，流浪汉。 -- Be careful, wanderer.}
#{1199}{}{Shh! Now is not the time to talk, wanderer. I must complete my daily ritual.}
{1199}{}{嘘！现在不是谈话的时候，流浪者。我必须完成每天的例行公事。 -- Shh! Now is not the time to talk, wanderer. I must complete my daily ritual.}
#{1202}{}{Everyone! Our hero returns!}
{1202}{}{所有人！我们的英雄回来了！ -- Everyone! Our hero returns!}
#{1210}{}{Hmm... That place is normally forbidden to outsiders. Only there, may we be alone to perform our most sacred worship. But you deserve our trust, wanderer. I cannot take you, but I will tell you where it is.}
{1210}{}{隐马尔可夫模型。。。那个地方通常禁止外人进入。只有在那里，我们才能独自一人进行我们最神圣的崇拜。但你值得我们信任，流浪者。我不能带你去，但我会告诉你在哪儿。 -- Hmm... That place is normally forbidden to outsiders. Only there, may we be alone to perform our most sacred worship. But you deserve our trust, wanderer. I cannot take you, but I will tell you where it is.}
#{1211}{}{Fine, I'll find it myself.}
{1211}{}{好吧，我自己去找。 -- Fine, I'll find it myself.}
